Work directly with the DPI to identify opportunities to maximize Matchforce, eTapestry, software cross-functionality, and the use of other databases and software to best serve our program and revenue goal.
Collaborate with the Leadership team on calculating annual agency-wide statistics to be used for internal and external communications.
Work with the Finance Director to align financial reporting with program outcomes and impact.
Participate in trainings and/or continuing education on relevant material for professional development.
Support, and collaborate with, other departments, including program, development, and Mission Support, along with the agency’s JEDI efforts, to accomplish organization goals.
Other duties as assigned by supervisor or CEO.

Relationship Building: Able to deal effectively with people in order to get work accomplished; adjust own interpersonal approach to fit the style/needs of others; recognize the impact of one’s behavior on others; utilize technical and business contacts to meet job responsibilities; network to reach specific influential people.
Values Diversity: Able to seek out and work effectively with others who have diverse perspectives, talents, backgrounds, and/or styles; contribute to a team climate in which differences are valued and supported; challenge any stereotyping or offensive comments; seek and respond to feedback from others about own behavior that might be perceived as biased.

This position is responsible for the integration and maintenance of district database systems and state of Montana databases to meet state-mandated district business and reporting requirements. Provide business analysis and system integration with various department heads for accurate reporting and data readiness of responsible programs
Collaborate with district administrators to compile, upload and certify data collections throughout the year.

     Job Description
    


Overall Purpose and Objective of Position  Verify and compile records on certificated cotton, gin cotton and all inbound and outbound cotton activity. Coordinate certificated cotton activities with all area warehouses. Schedule loads for all LDC Warehouses. Apply for all ME numbers from New York Board of Trade. Handle USDA classing and sample data. Responsible for shipping/receiving paperwork.
 Primary Responsibilities/Essential Functions

Compare identifying information, counts and weights of incoming and outgoing shipments of cotton to verify against Bills of Lading, invoices, orders or other records.
Extract data using special applications and software such as eCotton and Power BI.
Respond to data-related queries.
Help management identify and create processes to make data processing more efficient.
Perform analysis to assess the quality and meaning of data.
Process and schedule loads through eCotton on behalf of each LDCCS facility.
Process and maintain all data in regard to maintaining licensing insurance and other compliance activities for all LDCCS facilities.
Post weights and shipping charges, key into computer as to appropriate customer.
Record shortage and damage to cotton. Correspond with customer to rectify damages and shortages. Address complaints concerning billing or services rendered.
Ensure shipment meets specifications of accuracy, completeness and condition of product.
Maintain inventory of Stock and Block cotton, plus issue reports as required to customer. Complete stock reports by compiling inbound and outbound information on Stock and Block cotton.
Prepare invoices and bills of lading, lists weight and identifying number of cotton, plus additional certification billing.
Input and retrieve data from the computer. Read computer files and gather records to compile needed data.
Process job orders to determine work priorities.
Issue and transmit all receipts via EWR as well as cancel receipts daily of all shipped bales.


Collaborate with management to develop, review, and update Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs) for data processing and analysis, ensuring data integrity, best practices, and compliance with regulatory requirements.


Develop and maintain troubleshooting documents for data processing and analysis procedures, documenting common issues, root causes, and resolutions to ensure efficient problem-solving and minimize downtime in data operations.


Ensure the integration of accounting transactions across systems and departments and timely issuance of invoices, as well as the collection of payments from customers within established terms and minimize outstanding receivables.


Perform all related responsibilities as required.

Broad range of computer skills including functional knowledge of Microsoft programs, especially MS Word, Excel and Power Point. Microsoft Access, OneNote, SharePoint and Power BI will be beneficial.

WHO WE ARE:
CRLA was founded in 1966 to fight for justice and protect the rights of the most vulnerable people in our society. Through our network of regional offices and programs, we provide essential legal services to tens of thousands of low-income individuals every year. Our work positively impacts farmworkers, Indigenous communities, people with disabilities, immigrants, LGBTQ+ individuals, women, children, and low-income families living in rural areas.


Position: Data Analyst
Experience: Two (2) + years
Application Deadline: Open until filled
Location: Fully Remote, Located in California
Other: FLSA Exempt, Full-Time (37.5 hrs per week)


The Data Analyst will play a crucial role in supporting CRLA's mission by collecting, analyzing, and interpreting data to inform program development, decision-making, and reporting. Reporting to the Director of Data and Evaluation in a growing department, the person in this full-time position will work closely with stakeholders across and beyond the organization to ensure data quality, accuracy, and accessibility.
 Essential Responsibilities/Duties:

Collect and organize data from various sources, including surveys, case management systems, and external databases.
Build (or assist the building of) data collection tools (like surveys) to support the organizations reporting needs.
Develop and implement data quality checks and procedures.


Develop and maintain data-driven reports for internal and external audiences.
Clean and prepare data for analysis (including for annual reports/audits), ensuring data accuracy, reliability, and consistency.
Conduct data analysis using appropriate methods and tools.
Identify trends, patterns, and insights within the data.
Create visualizations (e.g., charts, graphs) to communicate data findings effectively.
Review, troubleshoot, and test system configurations in our case management system (LegalServer) as they relate to reporting and analytics.
Collaborate with stakeholders to translate data findings into actionable recommendations.
Serve as the data liaison, working with IT and program staff and other stakeholders to define, document, test, and implement data requirements in our case management system (LegalServer).
Create user-friendly, plain-language training materials and documentation for data access and analysis.
Document, track, and effectively communicate data-related challenges and opportunities.


 Education and Experience: 

2+ years of experience working with data and case management systems, OR 2+ years of experience with deep program knowledge, a strong ability to contextualize data, and a strong willingness to learn new technical and data skills (required)
Strong analytical and troubleshooting skills (required).
An understanding of data privacy and security best practices (or experience working with highly sensitive information) (required)
Creativity and problem-solving skills (required).
Excellent communication and collaboration skills (required).
Attention to detail and a commitment to accuracy (required).
Ability to work well independently and with a team (required).
Reliable access to high-speed internet (since this position will be remote/hybrid) (required).
Passion for continuous learning (learning agility) (preferred).
Proficiency in data analysis tools (e.g., Excel, PowerBI, CMS systems) (preferred).
Some basic project management skills (preferred)


 Compensation & Benefits:
We offer a diverse, family-friendly environment and compensation based on competitive public interest salaries. The estimated starting salary for this position is between $70,000 and $88,500, depending on any related work experience prior. Generous benefits package includes 100% employer-covered medical, dental, vision, life, and short & long-term disability insurance for employees and up to 50% for dependent coverage. A 401K retirement plan with a CRLA contribution is effective immediately. The generous paid leave policy includes 15 days of sick leave, 15 holidays each year (including a birthday holiday), and vacation (accrue 15 days for the first year of service and 20 days after one year of service at CRLA). We also have a Personal Wellness Day policy, which permits the use of up to 7.5 consecutive (sick) hours, or one working day, to be used each month to promote mental health and wellness.

CRLA requires that all employees be Fully Vaccinated, defined as a CDC-approved COVID vaccination and one booster shot. This offer is contingent on meeting this requirement. The complete vaccination policy, including the process for reasonable allowable accommodations, is available for your review upon request.

This position will be fully remote with the expectation of some (reimbursed) travel/in-person work for things like annual conferences, training opportunities, and team-building retreats. The data department typically works a standard business schedule (i.e., 8am-4pm or 9am-5pm, Monday through Friday), but there is flexibility. Candidate has to be located in California.

We are committed to building a culturally diverse workplace and very strongly encourage women, persons of color, LGBTQ+ individuals, veterans, persons with disabilities, and persons from other underrepresented groups to apply.

About Us



 Who We Are
At Raise the Future, we believe every young person goes through life knowing they have a caring adult by their side. So, every day, we show up for kids in foster care by listening to their needs and introducing them to adults they can rely on. We then surround those connections with support so that they grow into meaningful, lasting relationships that help our youth heal from the past. Because to truly raise the future, we must raise the bar for what it means to support vulnerable youth and families as they navigate life, and work to transform the systems they engage with.

Since our founding in 1983, Raise the Future has designed and implemented evidence-based, wraparound services that reduce the amount of time youth in foster care live without a permanent family. We also offer programs that sustain the connections made between youth and caring adults so that they can have positive, permanent relationships that transform their futures.

Your Why?
The idea of waking up every day to support children and families who need it most fills your cup. You believe deeply in the potential of our work to transform lives because you also believe in the promise of the children we serve. You see diversity, equity, and inclusion as values and mission imperatives. When asked, those in your orbit consistently say they feel seen, supported, and elevated by you. You take responsibility for your role, and you also believe that teamwork and partnership are where it's at. Your curiosity and creativity allow you to handle just about anything that comes your way. Youre seeking an organization where you can learn and grow as you help your colleagues and clients do the same, and you've found it.

Welcome to Raise the Future. We're glad you're interested in this role on our team! We have an exciting plan to amplify and accelerate our work and our data team will be a key player in continuing an evolution to meet those goals.




 Job Description



 The Data Analyst I understands how important it is to show that what we do at Raise the Future matters. This person thrives on making complex data simple, showing funders the impact of our work, and providing a continuous improvement loop with our Program staff. This position is a critical member of the Operations team, working closely with the team on data management, and they will ensure that the organizations program data is collected and stored properly to create accurate and useful applications for both internal and external customers. The Data Analyst I responds to recurring and ad hoc requests for data/information, and they work with the data team to ensure the entire data process, from collection to analysis, is efficient, meets the needs of all Raise the Futures unique audiences, and helps tell the story of our impact.




 Essential Duties and Responsibilities



 Note: This job description is intended to describe the general nature and level of work performed and is not to be construed as an exhaustive list of responsibilities, duties, and skills required. Other duties may be assigned. Furthermore, it does not establish a contract of employment and is subject to change at the discretion of the employer.

Prepare mandatory and ad hoc analyses and reports for leadership, state/federal agencies, development, and other external constituencies.


Organize, combine, summarize, and analyze data about the child welfare system and/or programs from a variety of sources, including identification of new sources as needed

About Lukos


  Lukos has been delivering professional services to the Federal Government for 15 years. We help a variety of federal agencies in areas such as national security, homeland security, international development, training, analytics, healthcare, and other professional services. Since our founding, we have grown to support all military services and multiple federal civilian agencies.
 

  About Our Name: Lukos is ancient Greek for “wolf”. The characteristics of the wolf match our approach to national security. The wolf is known for cunning, aggression, patience, and teamwork. Blueridge Dynamic Solutions is seeking a Data Analyst/Tableau Developer to work on site St. Louis MO. W2 Position.
Responsibilities
Develop. Acquire. Launch. Operate.
Our ideal Data Analyst will be an experienced core member of a dynamic team. Our Data and Analytics team help clients maximize the value of their data. This high performing team helps clients define their information strategy, architecture, and governance. This allows them to get the most value from business intelligence, analytics, and implement enterprise content and data management solutions. This will enable business insights, reduce costs and complexities, increase trust and integrity, and improve operational effectiveness.
Qualifications

Minimum Degree Required: Bachelor's degree in Economics, Statistics, Operations Research, Computer Science, Information Systems, Engineering, or similar quantitative discipline
Knowledge of Tableau Desktop and Tableau Server

Knowledge Preferred
Demonstrates thorough knowledge of, and proven success with a role, executing various aspects of the business or information technology-related client engagements and/or projects within a professional services environment, including knowledge of an industry or functional domain and expertise in at least two of the following areas:

Statistical Analysis and Techniques
Customer, Product, and Pricing Analysis
Business and Operations Analysis within marketing, operations, or risk analysis using quantitative techniques

Demonstrates significant experience working with analytical models or techniques and the ability to apply such methods to an applicable challenge within the larger field of expertise.

Advanced analytics techniques (regression, simulation, etc.)
Applicable sources of external, internal or new data sources to support analytic methods and visualization techniques
Customer an industrial Products and Services, Manufacturing or Telecom Industries

Skills Preferred
Demonstrates thorough skills and/or proven success in a role participating in consulting-related projects within a professional services environment that utilize creative thinking skills and individual initiative, including the following:

Analyzing large and complex data sets, including a demonstrated thorough aptitude for conducting quantitative and qualitative analyses
Experience with SQL, R and/or Python is a plus
Collaborating and contributing as a team member: understanding personal and team roles, contributing to a positive working environment by building solid relationships with team members, proactively seeking guidance, clarification, and feedback
Identifying and addressing client needs, building relationships with clients, developing requests for information, demonstrating flexibility in prioritizing, and completing tasks, communicating potential conflicts to a supervisor
Prioritizing and handling multiple tasks, researching, and analyzing pertinent client, industry and technical matters, utilizing problem-solving skills, and communicating effectively in written and verbal formats to various audiences (including various levels of management and external clients) in a professional business environment
Coaching and collaborating with associates who assist with this work, including providing coaching, feedback, and guidance on work performance
Understanding how the application of analytical techniques correlated to business value
Being able to select the appropriate analytical techniques for the problem at hand

Skills
- Tableau- Power BI- Database design- Agile- SQL- Visio- SDLC- Data analysis
